.container
    .jumbotron.subhead
        %h1= @page_title = "Modules"
        %p.lead General
    %section
        .row
            = partial('modules_sidebar')
            .col-sm-9
                .page-header
                    %h1= @page_sub_title = "Main Map Element"
                :markdown
                    Every map XML file must contain the base `<map>` module. It contains modules that specify the map name, version, objective, authors, contributors and all other map settings. The objective is the text that players see when they join the match, and so it's important for this to be very clear, concise, and informative.

                    The `proto=""` attribute specifies what PGM version the XML file was created for. If this value is higher than the version of PGM that is running, the map won't load. If it's lower, the map will load but the XML may be interpreted in an outdated way. Mapmakers should always use the latest supported XML version, and this may be required of new maps that are to be added to the Overcast Network rotations.

                    The maps version should follow the versioning schema `major.minor.patch`.

                %h5 Map Attributes
                .table-responsive
                    %table.table.table-striped.table-condensed
                        %thead
                            %tr
                                %th Attribute
                                %th Description
                                %th Value
                                %th Default
                        %tbody
                            %tr{:title => "Required"}
                                %td
                                    %code proto
                                %td The maps XML protocol version.
                                %td
                                    %code #{$map_proto}
                                    %span.label.label-danger Required
                                %td
                            %tr
                                %td
                                    %code internal
                                %td Prevent compass teleports above Y 255
                                %td
                                    %span.label.label-primary true/false
                                %td false

                %h5 Map Sub-elements
                .table-responsive
                    %table.table.table-striped.table-condensed
                        %thead
                            %tr
                                %th Element
                                %th Description
                                %th Value/Children
                        %tbody
                            %tr{:title => "Required"}
                                %td
                                    %pre
                                        %code= html_escape('<name>')
                                %td
                                    The name of the map.
                                %td
                                    %span.label.label-primary String
                                    %span.label.label-danger Required
                            %tr{:title => "Required"}
                                %td
                                    %pre
                                        %code= html_escape('<version>')
                                %td
                                    The map's
                                    %a{:href => "http://semver.org"} semantic version
                                    string.

                                %td
                                    %span.label.label-primary 1.0.0
                                    %span.label.label-danger Required
                            %tr{:title => "Required"}
                                %td
                                    %pre
                                        %code= html_escape('<objective>')
                                %td
                                    The map's objective, shown at the start of the match.
                                %td
                                    %span.label.label-primary String
                                    %span.label.label-danger Required
                            %tr{:title => "Required, at least one map author is required"}
                                %td
                                    %pre
                                        %code= html_escape('<authors>')
                                %td
                                    The authors of the map, at least one author is required.
                                %td
                                    %code= html_escape('<author>')
                                    %span.label.label-danger Required
                            %tr
                                %td
                                    %pre
                                        %code= html_escape('<contributors>')
                                %td
                                    Contributors to the map.
                                %td
                                    %code= html_escape('<contributor>')
                :markdown

                        <?xml version="1.0"?>
                        <map proto="#{$map_proto}">
                        <name>Map Name</name>
                        <version>1.0.0</version>
                        <objective>Short description about the maps objective.</objective>

                        <!-- Map authors & contributors. -->

                        <!-- Map modules, i.e. objectives, regions, spawns. -->

                        </map>

                :markdown
                    <br/>
                    #### Authors & Contributors
                    The authors and contributers elements provide information about who created and helped create the map. There can be multiple authors and contributors to a map. The contribution attribute should be used to specify what their contribution to the map was. It is recommended that you use the persons minecraft name to credit them.

                %h5 Author or Contributor Sub-elements
                .table-responsive
                    %table.table.table-striped.table-condensed
                        %thead
                            %tr
                                %th Element
                                %th Description
                                %th Value/Children
                        %tbody
                            %tr{:title => "Required, at least one map author is required"}
                                %td
                                    %pre
                                        %code= html_escape('<author>')
                                %td
                                    A major author of the map, used in
                                    %code= html_escape('<authors>')
                                %td
                                    %span.label.label-primary String
                                    %span.label.label-danger Required
                            %tr
                                %td
                                    %pre
                                        %code= html_escape('<contributor>')
                                %td
                                    A contributor to the map. used in
                                    %code= html_escape('<contributors>')

                                %td
                                    %span.label.label-primary String

                %h5 Author & Contributor Attributes
                .table-responsive
                    %table.table.table-striped.table-condensed
                        %thead
                            %tr
                                %th Attribute
                                %th Description
                                %th Value
                        %tbody
                            %tr
                                %td
                                    %code contribution
                                %td The contribution this author or contributor made to the map.
                                %td
                                    %span.label.label-primary String
                            %tr
                                %td
                                    %code uuid
                                %td UUID used to define a player.
                                %td
                                    %span.label.label-primary String

                %br
                A players UUID is a unique code to each player that is used to keep track of each player even if they change their name. You can check player UUID's on
                = succeed "." do
                    %a{:href => "http://mcuuid.net/"} mcuuid.net
                %br
                If you define a UUID and a username, the UUID will take priority - however if there is a problem getting the username from the UUID (there never should) it will use the username specified.
                %br

                :markdown

                        <!-- Major map authors. -->
                        <authors>
                            <author>aPerson</author>
                            <author contribution="Clarification of element usage, etc.">Plastix</author>
                            <author uuid="260004f0-996b-4539-ba21-df4ee6336b63">Elliott_</author>
                        </authors>

                        <!-- People that contributed in some way to the map. -->
                        <contributors>
                            <contributor contribution="A contribution">aHelper</contributor>
                        </contributors>
